title: Bryce Williams (rugby union)
text:
Bryce Williams (born 14 April 1980 in <a href="Dargaville">Dargaville</a>, <a href="New%20Zealand">New Zealand</a>) is a former <a href="rugby%20union">rugby union</a> player who played for <a href="Northland%20Rugby%20Football%20Union">Northland</a> in the <a href="ITM%20Cup">ITM Cup</a> competition.
Playing career.
Williams spent five seasons with <a href="Auckland%20Rugby%20Union">Auckland</a> and played briefly in <a href="Super%20Rugby">Super Rugby</a> for the <a href="Blues%20%28Super%20Rugby%20franchise%29">Blues</a> and <a href="Crusaders%20%28rugby%29">Crusaders</a>. He moved to Europe in 2005, spending a season with <a href="Leinster%20Rugby">Leinster</a> in the <a href="Pro14">Celtic League</a> and five seasons with <a href="CS%20Bourgoin-Jallieu">Bourgoin</a> in the French <a href="Top%2014">Top 14</a>.
Williams returned to New Zealand in 2011, signing with <a href="Northland%20Rugby%20Union">Northland</a> for the <a href="2011%20ITM%20Cup">2011 ITM Cup</a> and continued as a squad regular before retiring in 2014.
